task.summary: Default task
Major changes in the structure of the files, added Layers.py
Starting to work on Highermost layer
Implemented layer without local layers; Loaded Importer

First successful model run. Now, need to import the data correctly, and then modify the model to capture the real model of the paper. Finally, need to create a measure for the accuracy (using cross-validation e.g.)
Importer class seems to be done
Before refactoring. Refactoring is needed because we cannot save the weights in-between sessions yet, and we should look at how difference people implemented tensorflow models.
Debugged the 'accuracy shows ones only' bug
Everything is breaking... need to start my macbook
Saver and restorer implemented
Uploading first test on AlFRED
First full implementation. Need to check smaller variables/parameters, and also see if current implementation is correct.
Confusion matrix implemented.
Refactored code structure and some content, reassigned TODOs
Starting to implement a cross-session/cross-subject server
First tries to implement a data-handler to automatically handle cross-session and cross-subject data. It might be wiser, however, to do this pre-processing in the string-read-in stage.
Implementing cross validation for cross-subject, cross-session and intra-session. Still in developement!
First Cross-subject implementation. Needs some refactoring / restructuring / beautification / de-uglyization
Cross-session validation implemented but not tested. Testing needed once internet is back on.
Working on intra-session, cross-session still not tested. Entering plane
Cross-session implemented.
I think final model was implemented. Need logging system and refactoring
Voting implemented. Need to implement logging and check for semantic bugs.
Logging within the cross-subject part was implemented. A bug where a wrong value was divided from the difference_vector (accuracy voting) was debugged.
Reimplemented from Scratch, a first version that has 'verified' individual parts. Need to connect those individual parts now. Learned a lot on what to do better next time.
Saver implemented. Need to test convergence. Need to implement step-function where needed.

Convergence_tester implemented. I suspect we have too little training data to test for accuracy-increase, but the model seems to be implemented the way it is described in the paper. As such, we will implement sess.run within training, upload and then debug if we have convergence problems.
I found why it 'didn't converge'. I was just studip once more. Session was not used, but random guessing was.
Ready to set up intra-session on AlFRED
Prettified Logging.
